main event: A meteor was observed over Colorado Springs, Colorado on 21 April 1951.
interesting points: The conclusion of the report was that the object was an astronomical phenomenon, identified as a meteor., The meteor was noted to have a fast, straight, and level course., The report was part of the United States Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation into UFO sightings., There were no photographs included in the report., The observation lasted approximately 10 seconds.
